    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The main question to answer here is whether this trade-off makes sense for a production client. \r\n\r\nThere are 3 possible combinations of storing collation data in memory:\r\n- Store serialized body and a list of transactions. No serialization/deserialization needed for all usages of a collation\r\n- Store serialized body only. Deserialization necessary to inspect the contents of the collation.\r\n- Store list of transactions only. Serialization necessary when transmitting, saving, or verifying proofs of a collation. \r\n\r\n",
